Liseut, lunar bard of 51 songs <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarathena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arathena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Valkyrie of Innoruuk</span><br>  Posts: 447<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/15/02 7:44:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to run a sucessful Fear portal break...lookin for ad</span><hr size=1> Well, I'm not the best qualified to comment on a Fear portal break, as I've never been on a successful break, only one horrid, horrid flop, but, here's how I'd run one.<br>
<br>
The single most important thing is levels. If you want a portal break, get as many 55+ melees, healers, and most importantly, enchanters as you possibly can. If you can't make at least three groups with a cleric, 55+ warrior/knight, and 55+ enchanter,  you're going to have some severe problems handling the ten to 20 mobs that will be in camp immediately. Dealing with these mobs is going to require something other than your typical whole raid on one mob tactic. It's rather better to have each specific group fighting a different mob. Each mob may now last a minute instead of 15 seconds, but that's that much less excess mob that needs to be locked down by your enchanters. A typical fear raid should be able to put together about 5 groups each capable of taking on one fear mob. <br>
<br>
The key to a fear break is crowd control, and if you don't have enchanters that can handle 20 mobs, you'd best have tanks for 20 mobs.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21387">Arathena Validor</a><br>58th Reveness of Innoruuk, <br>
Poison Arrow<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unjorlsbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NjorlsBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/15/02 8:52:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to run a sucessful Fear portal break...lookin for ad</span><hr size=1> Have everyone invis. Stagger groups zoning in, 40 people zoning into fear = linkdeaths, which are Very Bad (tm)<br>
<br>
Once you zone in, turn 90 degrees to the left (west), run to the zone wall. Bring anything that attacks you to the wall. Chanters mes, shamans slow, tanks do their thing.<br>
<br>
Glare lords and tent terrors are Very Bad (tm) as well. Their AE dispel will cancel the mes's of the other mobs.<br>
<br>
We've successfully done it with about 6 groups in high 50's. We've also successfully screwed it all up with 6 groups of 60's. People running the wrong way, aggroing a bunch of tent terrors, being the main cause of defeat. I'm pretty sure it had been done with a 50 level cap in the early days.<br>
<br>
It works great and is a lot of fun when it works, and is a big pain when it fails. Good luck.<br>
