<br>
2 teams zone in first, main raids holds at portal.<br>
<br>
Team 1<br>
Heavy Tank<br>
Heavy Tank<br>
Cleric<br>
Enchanter<br>
Bard<br>
Druid<br>
<br>
Team 2<br>
Heavy Tank<br>
Heavy Tank<br>
Cleric<br>
Enchanter<br>
Shaman<br>
Druid<br>
<br>
Most everyone 55+.  Have them take the 90 degree turn out of the portal and hit the wall just south of the FF house.  CC and Tank down whatever you have.  If the bard/chanters are good, you should be able to handle at least 6-8 mobs.  If things are hairy, have the druids evac and try again.  <br>
<br>
Once things are sorted out and half the mobs in camp are dead, have another team zone in and run to the spot.  Stagger the zone ins, and make damn sure everyone knows who to assist and where you are going.  Waste everything, clear FF, skip the North TT and Monkeys to save your buffs and pull south from the break in camp.  <br>
<br>
