</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubranndamere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Branndamere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/10/02 8:11:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to run a sucessful Fear portal break...lookin for ad</span><hr size=1> Hmm, lots of good advice here. Some things that will help make the break successful:<br>
<br>
Before you even zone in, make sure you state to your raid, very clearly, what the plan is. Portal breaks are made way more iffy when raiders don't follow instructions. <br>
<br>
Zone your groups in, in 5-second intervals, starting with the groups with the biggest, best-armored tanks/clerics/chanters.<br>
<br>
2 - 3 55+ enchanters with a strong connection, for minimal lag/LD problems. How do you get them to come along? Lots of chanters looking for that elusive Shissar head. Offer to let them roll on it.<br>
<br>
Make sure you have a cleric and a backup healer in each group with your key enchanters, in case one of the healers goes LD or dies.<br>
<br>
Also, make sure that all your healing classes know the names of the chanters, so they can /tar name them, to help heal them til they get all the mobs mezzed.<br>
<br>
I don't agree with having several groups take on one mob each, unless all the chanters die, and you have really strong groups. Better to kill one mob in 15 seconds and leave the others mezzed, then move to the next mob, imho.<br>
<br>
Make sure that everyone knows that once they zone into Fear, they IMMEDIATELY turn 90 degrees to the left and haul booty for the zone wall. Do NOT stop, even if you are attacked. Train the mobs to the zone wall, that's why you have the 55+ chanters along.<br>
<br>
If you run totally the wrong way and are all alone with a big train of mobs, go ahead and die. There's a good chance the rest of the raid already has its hands full at the zone wall. Make sure you get your loc.<br>
<br>
The mobs you can expect from a correct portal break are scarelings, shiverbacks, and spiderlings, for the most part.<br>
<br>
If you find yourself faced with having to do a portal break, unexpectedly, arrange for some assistance with some friends/guilds who have experience doing breaks. There are a few guilds around who don't do Fear very often anymore, but who may be looking for just the Broken Golem, Shissar, or other epic drops from Fear. A shot at one of these epic mobs would be a good trade for the learning experience and success you would gain, if you can get some good help.<br>
